         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (in) the 38th (week)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... it goes into solidity ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... all (limbs?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is attached to ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... these ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is attached to ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... ...-two ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... has arisen ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the wind of fate (<hi>karma</hi>) ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">A fragment from the left side of a leaf: upper, lower and left margins are preserved. Black lineage.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>l··</hi>: the <hi>l</hi> could be in a ligature, and it could have an <hi>ā</hi>-vowel. Thus, a restoration to <hi>lyā</hi> 'limbs' is a possibility, cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a150"/> b1 <hi>puk lyā āps·</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment"><hi>l rītwoṣ</hi>, <ref type="ms" target="#b1"/><hi>l rītwo(ṣ)</hi>: the <hi>l</hi> most probably is to be restored as a com. ending <hi>°(aśśä)l</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><hi>rpaṣi</hi>: probably a <hi>ṣi</hi>-adjective derived from a noun in <hi>-rp</hi>. According to <bibl><title corresp="ref:poucha1955"/><citedRange>434</citedRange></bibl>, there are only three possibilities: <hi>tarp</hi> 'pond', <hi>sparp</hi> 'rope', and <hi>warp</hi> 'enclosure'.</note><note corresp="#a6" type="philcomment">: cf. e.g. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a150"/> b4 <hi>cesäm ṣpät koṃsā</hi> 'by this week', lit. 'by these seven days'.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment"><hi>lypurṣi wa·t</hi>: even though the element before the <hi>t</hi> is illegible, a reading <hi>wa(n)t</hi> is suggested by the expression 'wind of fate' in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a148"/> a2 <hi>lyalypurṣināṃ waṃtyo</hi> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a341"/> a7 <hi>lyalypurṣi want</hi>. <hi>ca</hi> could have to be restored to <hi>ca(mi)</hi> 'its, his', among others.</note></p>
         </div>
